added.title: La Larva de Amor
added.description: The gang agrees to babysit Silkie but then loses him. Meanwhile, Silkie has a telenovela adventure south of the border.

added.title: Ghostboy
added.description: Starfire mistakenly thinks she's killed Beast Boy, leading him to pose as a ghost and torment her.

added.title: Books
added.description: Raven shows the rest of the Titans that books can be fun.

added.title: Lazy Sunday
added.description: When the Titans replace the couch with a treadmill, Cyborg and Beast Boy must get guidance from the couch spirit.

added.title: The Left Leg
added.description: When the gang bands together to form a giant robot, Robin is relegated to the left leg - but he makes the left leg count!

added.title: The Founder
added.description: When Nicole decides to pay the cable bill in person at Chanax, she leaves specific instructions for Richard to stay in the car. However he's far too tempted by the vending machine in the foyer to follow her advice. Chanax believes Richard is their mysterious founder and follow his every whim, leading to their inevitable demise.

added.title: The Schooling
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are at the convenience store considering playing truant. Larry warns them that if they don't take their education seriously they'll end up like him. To prove his point, Larry lets Gumball and Darwin work some of his many roles to make them appreciate the value of a good education.

added.title: The Intelligence
added.description: Gumball and Darwin argue with the Internet and make him mad. So mad in fact that he seeks to wipe out humanity and, while doing so, malfunctions! The whole of Elmore is plunged into a time before technology. It's actually pretty nice. Will Gumball and Darwin decide to leave the internet unplugged?

added.title: The Potion
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that Hector is not so happy being giant-sized. So they decide to help him by creating a potion that will shrink him down to the size of an average person. However creating a magic potion is not as easy as it sounds, and the results can go spectacularly wrong...

added.title: The Spinoffs
added.description: Wishing to get rid of Gumball once and for all, his nemesis Rob offers up a variety of reality, action and comedy shows featuring characters other than Gumball. Unfortunately for Rob, each one is worse than the last.

added.title: The Cursed Word
added.description: Craig uncovers an ancient Creek Curse.

added.title: Craiggy & the Slime Factory
added.description: Craig and his friends get the first ever tour of the Slime Kids Slime Factory.

added.title: Memories of Bobby
added.description: When a pillar of the Creek community leaves, our trio mourns their loss by remembering the good times.

added.title: Jacob of the Creek
added.description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

added.title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
added.description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

added.title: Kelsey the Author
added.description: Craig and Stacks help Kelsey become a real author turning her story into a book!

added.title: Sheep Bears
added.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

added.title: Ice Bear's Pet
added.description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: No Land, All Air!
added.description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

added.title: Tooth Fairy Tech
added.description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

added.title: Exercising the Demons
added.description: When a severe screen addiction turns the kids into lazy deadbeats, Chef brings in a professional to whip them into shape.

added.title: Pudding the Planet First
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Supply Mom
added.description: When Chef's mom becomes the supply teacher for a day Duncan replaces Chef's to-do list with one of his own.

added.title: Mooshy Mon Mons
added.description: After eating Chef's extremely rare and expensive chocolates Courtney drags Owen, Izzy and Beth all the way to the Norberian Alps of Fruffenberg to replace them.

added.title: Student Becomes the Teacher
added.description: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

added.title: Pat on the Head
added.description: Apple and Onion are to cook for a very important guest but Onion is not quite feeling himself.

added.title: Falafel's Glory
added.description: Apple and Onion must recruit the help of retired quiz master Falafel if they are to not starve.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

added.title: Microwave's Dance Club
added.description: DJ Saltfish and MC Ackee are in town for two nights only and Apple and Onion are determined to make the most of it and bust some moves on the dance floor.

added.title: Funhouse
added.description: The Tennysons find themselves stuck inside an inescapable funhouse constructed by Zombozo; Ben goes alien and fights for escape, ultimately proving that behind every illusion, there's a disappointing secret.

added.title: Summer Breakers
added.description: After Grandpa Max's super smart buddy Phil discovers that a second extraterrestrial item crashed alongside the Omnitrix, Team Tennyson sets off to find the second crash site before someone else does but arrive instead to find nefarious newcomer Breaker One-Nine has already beat them to the punch.

added.title: The Monsters in Your Head
added.description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

added.title: Queen of Bees
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Grandpa Max arrive in Bismarck, North Dakota for its annual celebration of bee pollination, bringing them face-to-face with Queen Bee and a bold new scheme, forcing Ben to conquer his new fear of bees!

added.title: Gentle Ben
added.description: Grandpa Max's alma mater asks him to use the Omni-Copter to transport an important exhibit to an exotic nature reserve, but when the exhibit turns out to be a rare and very large baby moth, Ben must keep Tim Buktu from stealing the moth while learning that sometimes you need to use finesse and not force to solve hard problems.

added.title: The Galactic Enforcers
added.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Bros in Space
added.description: Rook brings Ben to his home planet to meet the family. Unbeknownst to them, an old foe is raising an army to steal the planet's most precious resource!  (Introducing Rook's family.)

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: Sadie's Song
added.description: Steven helps Sadie put together an act for Beachapalooza.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: When It Rains
added.description: Steven helps a friend who's afraid of thunderstorms.

added.title: Back to the Barn
added.description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn to build some robots.

added.title: Too Far
added.description: Amethyst and Steven get in on some Gem gossip.

added.title: Frost & Fire
added.description: After Flame Princess battles Ice King, Finn has an exciting dream. But when it abruptly ends, Finn must get Flame Princess and Ice King to fight again to find out how it ends.

added.title: Too Old
added.description: Finn, Jake and Princess Bubblegum discover a talented mutant named Lemonsqueak at the Pageant of Mutants. Now, they must find a way to free him from the Lemongrabs.

added.title: Earth & Water
added.description: Princess Bubblegum subjects Flame Princess to a series of tests to gauge Flame Princess's fiery tendencies. When there's an emergency at the treehouse and Princess Bubblegum leaves Cinnamon Bun to watch Flame Princess, her experiment might literally backfire in her face.

added.title: Time Sandwich
added.description: Jake crafts the most delicious sandwich ever, but when Magic Man steals it, Finn must defy the laws of space and time to win back Jake's creation.

added.title: The Vault
added.description: When Finn starts sleepwalking and dreaming about the Green Lady he filed away in his memory vault, Jake and BMO help him tap into his repressed memories to uncover a secret past.

added.title: Pool Duel
added.description: Unikitty and the gang are having a great time at the public pool, until they try to get Puppycorn to swim in the deep end with them. Puppycorn is terrified of the deep end. Now Unikitty and the gang must get him over his fear, so he can have maximum pool fun. Meanwhile, Master Frown and Brock are hatching a plan to ruin everyone's fun, by pulling the pool's plug.

added.title: This Spells Disaster
added.description: The gang is planning a surprise for Puppycorn, so they spell things out when talking so he won't find out. Desperate to know what they're saying, Puppycorn finds a magic book that he thinks will help him learn to spell, but unbeknownst to him, it's teaching him how to cast spells! Will Puppycorn realize that knowledge is power and some secrets are kept for a reason?

added.title: Roadtrip Ruckus
added.description: Richard has decided to take Unikitty and the gang for a pleasant and relaxing 10 hour road trip. At first everyone is against the trip, but they soon start to have fun. Unfortunately, their idea of fun is not Richard's.  He soon begins to give in to his inner road-rage. To make matters worse they are being chased by a killer semi-truck, and their car has been invaded by weird bug hitchhiker.  Will Richard loose it, or will the trip be a great success?

added.title: Memory Amok
added.description: When Puppycorn witnesses Unikitty do the most embarrassing thing ever, he vows he will never forget it. Desperate, Unikitty uses Dr. Fox's memory machine to erase Puppycorn's memory of the embarrassing event. In the process, Unikitty accidentally releases all of Puppycorn's memories. Now she and the gang must scramble to capture all the scampering memories, or Puppycorn will forget his life.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
added.description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

added.title: Silent Treatment/Sweet "n" Sour
added.description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Midnight at the Mayor's Mansion
added.description: When the Mayor's mansion is stalked by a vicious, ghostly monster, he calls the Powerpuff Girls for help.

added.title: Derby Dollies
added.description: When Bubbles joins the Derbytantes, Buttercup finds herself on the sidelines.

added.title: Bubbles the Blue
added.description: When Bubbles isn't her normal, bubbly self, her sisters don't know how to handle it.

added.title: Deb O'Nair
added.description: A classy queen of etiquette makes the Utoniums question their superhero way of life.

added.title: The Blossom Files
added.description: Blossom's skepticism is put to the test when she believes she's encountered a space alien.

added.title: Band of Outsiders
added.description: A gang of streetwise kids takes Baby Ice Bear under their wing.

added.title: Tabes & Charlie
added.description: Tabes and Charlie team up to find Tabes' missing dog, Kirk.

added.title: Coffee Cave
added.description: After finding out Ice Bear is a master barista, the Bears turn their cave into a popular coffee shop. But it all goes awry when Ice Bear gets too into coffee and goes berserk.

added.title: Charlie's Big Foot
added.description: After Charlie hurts his foot, The Bears have to sneak him into a hospital for medical assistance.

added.title: Skater Sumo
added.description: As Sumo and Clarence are playing outside, Chelsea and Rita skate by on their new skateboards. Enthralled, Sumo decides to build his own and join their skating team, while Clarence seems to have other ideas.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Dullance
added.description: Burned out from having so many adventures, Clarence struggles to sit around and do nothing.

added.title: Numbskull
added.description: A head Injury turns Mr. Gus into a bumbling fools whose wacky antics make him Uncle Grandpa's coolest friend. No longer the focus of Uncle Grandpa's attention, a jealous Pizza Steve tries to desperately to get back normal. Mr. Gus has to restore social balance in the RV.

added.title: Body Trouble
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Belly Bag have a disagreement, they separate and try to make each other jealous.

added.title: Shower Party
added.description: Things get out of hand when Andrew W. K. helps Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus throw a party while Uncle Grandpa is in the shower.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Land
added.description: Pizza Steve must find a way to sneak onto his own roller coaster at the newly opened Uncle Grandpa Land.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: The Maze of the Red Dragon
added.description: Still in the game zone Terra Kerana, the Samurai guide Okino has to choose between helping his allies the ninja, or obeying the evil orders of his Master, Unagami.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Racer Seven
added.description: As the ninja prepare for the brutal Speedway Five-Billion race, Lloyd meets a race driver named Seven, who is programmed to lose, but who may hold the key to victory.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: The Best Friend/Thief and Brawler
added.description: The Best Friend: The top four brawlers in the Bakugan Battle League have been decided. For this round of the semi-finals it's a battle of best friends: Wynton vs. Dan. The winner of this battle between best buddies will move on to the championship round./Thief and Brawler: In the final battle of the Bakugan Battle league semi-finals it's Shun vs. Ajit. It's a grueling battle of focus, will, and strength, only a true brawler to emerge victorious.

added.title: Final Battle! Dan vs. Ajit/Secrets Exposed
added.description: Final Battle! Dan vs. Ajit: It's time for the event everyone in Los Volmos has been waiting for, The Bakugan Battle League finals! It's the Awesome Brawler's Dan Kouzo vs. the golden Bakugan brawler Ajit, these two face-off in a final brawl for it all./Secrets Exposed: The Bakugan Battle League has ended, and the winner has been determined, but the celebration is cut short when Phantom Thief Storm crashes the party by stealing everyone's Bakugan! It's up to Dan and Ajit to stop Storm and return all the stolen Bakugan.

added.title: Here Comes Haavik/The Fusion Bakugan Arrive
added.description: Here Comes Haavik: An evil shapeshifting alien has landed in Los Volmos! If that wasn't bad enough, he has a group of robot mechanoids on his trail trying to bring him justice. Meanwhile, Dan has accepted a battle challenge from a pair of brawlers, Chad and Trey./The Fusion Bakugan Arrive: Still humiliated by their defeat, Chad and Trey challenge Dan to rematch but this time they have a few tricks up their sleeve, and a little help on their side.

added.title: The Director/Queen Ebony
added.description: The Director: Everett Ray reaches out to Lia with an opportunity that seems too good to be true. Everett is now working in show business and proposes to make Lia's dream of becoming a film director come true. He's taken care of all the arrangements; all Lia has to do is provide the directorial vision./Queen Ebony: On his daily jaunt, Lightning learns of a street cat named Ebony, who's been treating dogs like servants, threatening them to do her bidding or face the wrath of her Bakugan! Lightning tries to reason with Ebony but when that doesn't work, it turns into a cat vs. dog Bakugan brawl!

added.title: Sophie, the Bakuganist/Midnight Train Battle!
added.description: Sophie, the Bakuganist: Magnus is on the trail of the illegal Baku-brawling devices and, is looking to cut off the supply at its source. When he witnesses an illegal deal going down, he knows it's up to him to go after the shipment to keep the illegal devices off the street./Midnight Train Battle!: Sophie Judson Warfield, a wealthy activist with the Citizens to Save Bakugan Society, is working to put an end to all Bakugan brawling. Her latest target is the Awesome Brawlers themselves. When Wynton doesn't take Sophie seriously, the encounter quickly turns into an all-out Bakugan brawl.

added.title: Calmado Ben
added.description: El alma máter del abuelo Max le pide que utilice el Omnicóptero para transportar una pieza muy importante a una reserva natural de especies exóticas. Pero cuando la pieza resulta ser una polilla bebé rara y muy grande, Ben debe evitar que Tim Buktu se la robe.

added.title: Casa de la Risa
added.description: Los Tennyson se encuentran atrapados dentro de una casa de la risa construida por Zombozo, de la cual es imposible escapar; Ben se vuelve alienígena y lucha por escapar, y así demuestra que, a fin de cuentas, detrás de cada ilusión hay un secreto decepcionante.

added.title: Interrumpiendo el Verano
added.description: Cuando Phil, el brillante amigo del abuelo Max, descubre que un segundo objeto extraterrestre se estrelló junto al Omnitrix, el equipo Tennyson se pone en marcha para encontrar el segundo lugar de la colisión antes de otro lo haga.

added.title: Los Monstruos de tu Cabeza
added.description: Ben y Gwen se enteran del rumor de una invasión alienígena en el parque en el que están acampando, pero cuando investigan, descubren una reserva que contiene una gran cantidad de criaturas mutantes diseñadas por Animo.

added.title: Reina de las Abejas
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el abuelo Max visitan Bismarck, en Dakota del Norte, para la celebración anual del festival de abejas. Al encontrarse cara a cara con Abeja Reina y su nuevo plan, Ben debe conquistar su nuevo miedo a las abejas.

added.title: Ejercitando los Demonios
added.description: Cuando una severa adicción a las pantalla convierte a los niños en holgazanes, Chef trae a una profesional para ponerlos en forma.

added.title: Pudin-Pocalipsis
added.description: Después de que Chef dice que los puntos de vista contrarios hacen al mundo más interesante y divertido, Izzy lo aplica del peor modo posible.

added.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
added.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

added.title: Mama Suplente
added.description: Cuando la mamá de Chef se convierte en maestra suplente por un día, Duncan cambia la lista de actividades de Chef por la suya.

added.title: Mushi-Mon-Mon
added.description: Después de comer los muy costosos y raros chocolates de Chef, Courtney arrastra a Owen, Izzy y Beth hasta los Alpes Norberianos de Fruffenberg para reemplazarlos.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: El Estudiante se Hace Maestro
added.description: Chef queda insconsciente justo antes de que una evaluadora de la junta escolar aparezca para una inspección. Ahora Owen tiene que reemplazarlo para que Chef no pierda su licencia de maestro y para asegurar que los chicos ganen el paseo en pony que Chef les prometió por su buena conducta.

added.title: Piloto Siete
added.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: El Fundador
added.description: Papá desata un caos en el edificio Chanax cuando lo confunden con el presidente de la empresa, desaparecido hace tiempo. Mamá y un empleado insatisfecho deben salvar a todos de las ideas peligrosas de Richard.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Leccion
added.description: Gumball y Darwin se hacen cargo de los trabajos de Larry durante 5 minutos y se dan cuenta de lo desagradable que son.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Inteligencia
added.description: La tecnología alcanza el nivel de la inteligencia humana, y luego se vuelve disfuncional cuando imita sus defectos.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Pocion
added.description: Gumball y Darwin usan una poción mágica para encoger a Héctor.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Historias Alternas
added.description: Rob crea una variedad de programas y formatos derivados ambientados en Elmore para reemplazar a Gumball.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Duelo en la Piscina
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla se están divirtiendo mucho en la piscina pública, hasta que intentan que Perricornio nade en la parte profunda con ellos. A Perricornio le da muchísimo miedo ir a lo más profundo. Ahora Unikitty y la banda deben ayudarlo a superar su miedo para que se divierta al máximo en la piscina. Mientras tanto, Master Frown y Brock están tramando un plan para arruinar la diversión de todos: quitar el tapón de la piscina. Ahora Perricornio debe dominar su miedo para detener a los que quieren estropear la diversión.

added.title: Problemas Dentales
added.description: A Puppycorn se le cae su primer diente, y Unikitty está emocionada por su hermanito, ique ahora recibirá la visita de la legendaria Hada de los Dientes! Pero cuando el Hada de los Dientes no aparece, Unikitty y sus amigos asumen la responsabilidad. ¿Acaso se meterán demasiado rápido y con demasiada soltura con los dientes sueltos y tocarán un nervio sensible?

added.title: Letras Desastrosas
added.description: La pandilla está planeando una sorpresa para Puppycorn, así que deletrean las cosas cuando hablan para que él no se entere. Desesperado por saber lo que dicen, Puppycorn encuentra un libro mágico que cree que lo ayudará a aprender a deletrear, ipero sin saberlo, el libro le enseña a lanzar hechizos! ¿Se dará cuenta Puppycorn de que el conocimiento es poder, y de que algunos secretos se guardan por una razón?

added.title: Viaje en Carretera
added.description: Richard decidió llevar a Unikitty y a la banda a un agradable y relajante viaje de 10 horas por la carretera. Al principio todo el mundo está en contra del viaje, pero pronto empiezan a divertirse. Por desgracia, su idea de diversión no es la de Richard. Pronto, el conductor comienza a sucumbir ante su furia interior al volante. Para colmo de males, los persigue un semirremolque asesino, y su coche ha sido invadido por un extraño autoestopista. ¿Richard perderá la razón o el viaje será un gran éxito?

added.title: Recuerdos Locos
added.description: Cuando Perricornio ve a Unikitty hacer la cosa más vergonzosa de la historia, jura que nunca lo olvidará. Desesperada, Unikitty utiliza la máquina de memoria de la Dra. Fox para borrar el recuerdo de Perricornio del embarazoso evento. En el proceso, Unikitty libera accidentalmente todos los recuerdos de Perricornio. Ahora ella y su pandilla deben capturar todos los recuerdos de prisa, o Perricornio olvidará su vida.

added.title: Buff's BFF
added.description: When Buff befriends Mr. Freeze's snowcrawler Snowy, the other Batwheels bristle at the thought of hanging out with a "bad guy…" so Buff sets out to change their minds.

added.title: Up in the Air
added.description: After he causes the Batwing to crash, Bam becomes obsessed with making it up to her during a high-stakes aerial mission against Penguin and his giant ducky blimp.

added.title: MacBarm's Day Off/Playhouse Problems
added.description: It's MacBarm's day off and Zee takes over harvesting carrots with his Zee mobile, but when it breaks, the work still needs to be done./Ranger Nat is bringing a playhouse on the train for Timmy and Izzy, but it won't fit through the tunnel!

added.title: Can't Stop the Martians/Best Nest Test
added.description: The Martians come to Pretty Big City but find themselves in need of help when they are unable to land their spaceship./Zee needs to communicate with Sif in outer space but can't because a bird has made its home on top of the satellite dish!

added.title: Sir Topham Hatt's Hat
added.description: When Sir Topham Hatt's Hat blows away in the wind before making an important announcement, Thomas and his friends race around Sodor, trying to catch it. The Hat remains out of reach until they learn to work together.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Nia's Surprising Surprise
added.description: Nia is planning a big party to celebrate the anniversary of her arrival on Sodor, but she finds that her friends don't remember her anniversary and are too busy to even talk about it.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A New View for Thomas
added.description: When Thomas spends the day carrying rockstar idol Harold across Sodor, he gains a new perspective on just how amazing it is to be his engine-self.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Skiff Sails Sodor
added.description: When Skiff gets a crack in his hull, Thomas needs to move him overland to Harwick for repairs, but Skiff's land-sickness makes that challenging.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Song of Sodor
added.description: When Nia suggests adding a song to spice up Sir Topham Hatt's new bench unveiling, he calls upon her to write a song for the ceremony, but Nia soon finds she may have bitten off more than she can sing.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Gravity
added.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

added.title: Honey
added.description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

added.title: Ocean
added.description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

added.title: 5 Little Ducks - Playtime at the Farm!
added.description: Mia and Ella find a nest of baby ducks. Ella plays "Mummy Duck." Will they find their real mummy?

added.title: ABC Song - Learn Phonics
added.description: Dancing around the barn, characters pop up, each singing about a different letter of the alphabet.

added.title: Trick or Treat
added.description: Mei, Mummy and Ella (3 generations of the same family) are all trick or treating together around the CITY!

removed.title: Ninjago Confidencial
removed.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

removed.title: Dia de cosplay
removed.description: El Equipo Tennyson está disfrutando la mejor convención de la ciudad. Pero cuando un empleado torpe de una tienda de disfraces encuentra un casco de aspecto familiar en el fondo de la tienda y se lo prueba, Ben debe enfrentar el regreso de un viejo enemigo en una nueva forma: iel Caballero Eterno!

removed.title: Inodoro Real
removed.description: Cuando los otros chicos temen que Harold se haya descargado a sí mismo por accidente en el elegante inodoro nuevo de Chef, viajan al desagüe a rescatarlo. Pero, ¿encontrarán a Harold antes que el mítico Cocodrilo Rey los deje atrapados bajo tierra para siempre?

removed.title: Corriendo en Lodo
removed.description: Ben aprende una lección a la fuerza sobre sus propios límites cuando compite en una agotadora carrera de obstáculos, ique empeora aún más con la presencia de los Climáticos!

removed.title: El Padre Prodigo
removed.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

removed.title: Es tiempo de historias
removed.description: Cuando la Rustbucket se avería, Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max se ven obligados a pasar el rato en la biblioteca de esa ciudad. Pronto se esfuerzan por superar a Hex, que está buscando un artefacto antiguo oculto.

removed.title: Juego Terminado
removed.description: Unagami entra al mundo real y aterroriza a la ciudad de Ninjago mientras Jay, Zane y Pixal intentan evitar el desastre reuniendo a Unagami con Dyer.

removed.title: El Dia de la Pinata
removed.description: Izzy no logra golpear una piñata durante las celebraciones del Cinco de Mayo de la clase. Pero cuando esa piñata sin aplastar cobra vida y genera un ejército de piñatas malignas, es la hora de la verdad.

removed.title: El Templo de la Locura
removed.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

removed.title: Un Juego Peligroso
removed.description: Después de que Leshawna, Bridgette, Owen y Cody ganan una competencia de jugar al escondite, están atrapados en una isla privada por una antigua campeona celosa y tienen que jugar a su juego.

removed.title: Beth y la Planta de Frijoles
removed.description: Después de que Chef les confiscara una barra de chocolate, Beth se encuentra en un mundo paralelo gigante y quiere recuperar su barra que ahora es enorme.

removed.title: El Gran Lago
removed.description: Durante una visita al lago Erie, un día relajante de playa se transforma súbitamente cuando Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max quedan cara a cara con Hex y Kevin, su asistente de verano.

removed.title: Shintaro
removed.description: Los Ninjas están invitados a asistir a la fiesta de cumpleaños de la princesa Vania en la ciudad de Shintaro. Llevan al Maestro Wu que está deprimido.

removed.title: El Hada de los Gases
removed.description: Después de perder su primer diente flojo por accidente y temer el no tener efectivo bajo la almohada, Leshawna intenta capturar al hada de los dientes. En vez de eso, captura al hada de los gases. Esto trae grandes consecuencias.

removed.title: Cataratas y Caidas
removed.description: El equipo Tennyson visita las cascadas Shoshone para apreciar su belleza, pero al llegar, encuentran que Vapor Smythe ha estado extrayendo el agua de las cascadas. Depende de Ben, Gwen y el abuelo Max detener su plan y salvar las cascadas.

removed.title: While You Were Away
removed.description: Dr. Psychobos and Princess Attea have invaded Rook's home planet Revonnah with an army of Incurseans! (Introducing new Ben alien, Astrodactyl.)

removed.title: Vilgax Must Croak
removed.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

removed.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
removed.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

removed.title: Showdown Part 2
removed.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

removed.title: Tummy Trouble
removed.description: When the Incursean armada kidnaps the Gourmand Queen, Ben and Rook must get the warring Gormand factions to work together to save her and stop the Incursean invasion.

removed.title: Showdown Part I
removed.description: The Faction infiltrates Galvan in an attempt to destroy Azmuth.  (Introducing new Nemetrix aliens Omnivoracious & Vicetopus.)

removed.title: A Change of Face
removed.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

removed.title: Back with a Vengeance
removed.description: Ben's feeling cocky with the watch. He's unlocked its secret, and now can become any alien he wants, whenever he wants. That's the good news. The bad news is, after finding one another in the depths of space, Kevin 11 and Vilgax have teamed up and have returned to earth to destroy Ben and get the Omnitrix.

removed.title: Ben 10,000
removed.description: Ben gets sucked into the future by a grown up Gwen. His mission is to help the now all powerful and adult Ben 10,000 seemingly defeat the future versions of Dr. Animo and Vilgax. However, the real reason Ben has been brought to the future is to teach his adult self some humility and the fact he's lost touch with Max and has forgotten what's really important, family.

removed.title: Midnight Madness
removed.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

removed.title: Sidekicked to the Curb
removed.description: When Bam is sent to take on Prank, Redbird is forced to hang back because The Joker's van is too dangerous! When Bam discovers that Redbird secretly tagged along, he's upset… until Redbird bails him out of a tight spot.

removed.title: Thomas' Promise
removed.description: When Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the same load to Whiff's Recycling Plant, Thomas suggests they each take half of the load, but Diesel turns it into a race.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Do the Skeleton Dance - Halloween Special
removed.description: Lellobee City Farm learns to do the groovy Skeleton Dance for Halloween.

removed.title: Bedtime Song
removed.description: Ella is getting ready for bed for a sleepover at Mei's house

removed.title: Fruit & Vegetables
removed.description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

removed.title: Mountain
removed.description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

removed.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
removed.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

removed.title: Planets
removed.description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

removed.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
removed.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

removed.title: Get in Gear/Free-Wheelin' Ferris Wheel
removed.description: Panic erupts in Pretty Big City when the big clock breaks and no one is able to tell what time it is./Zee is showing off his inventions at his rocket-powered show, including his latest creation, a rocket powered Ferris wheel.

removed.title: Wheels on the Bus
removed.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

removed.title: Rules of the Game
removed.description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Bibi's Do-Over
removed.description: Everyone is ecstatic when Bibi, Batgirl, and Robin capture Toyman and his Do-Over remote - except for Bibi, who failed to stick the landing on a big jump. Unwilling to accept her failure, Bibi uses Toyman's Do-Over remote until she perfects her jump!

removed.title: License to Deliver
removed.description: When Percy has to deliver a new light bulb to the lighthouse at night, Thomas suggests playing secret agents along the way to help Percy forget about his fear of the dark.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: A Quiet Delivery
removed.description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Thomas Blasts Off
removed.description: It's rocket launch day and all the trains get to help deliver the big rocket parts, but when Thomas is assigned a tiny part, he puts it off to help the others with their more exciting parts, not realizing that his "small" task was just as important.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Cosplay Day
removed.description: Team Tennyson enjoy the biggest convention in town, but when a gawky costume store employee finds a familiar-looking helmet in the back of the store and tries it on, Ben is faced with the return of an old foe in a new form: Forever Knight!

removed.title: The Greatest Lake
removed.description: While visiting Lake Erie, a relaxing day at the beach gets all washed up when Ben, Gwen and Grandpa Max come face-to-face with Hex, and his summer intern, Kevin!

removed.title: Falls, Falls, Falls
removed.description: Team Tennyson looks to take in the sights of the Shoshone Falls, but when they arrive to find Steam Smythe siphoning off the water, it is up to Ben to distract the steam punk baddie long enough to allow Grandpa Max and Gwen the time to shut down the hydropower plant and save the Falls.

removed.title: It's Story Time
removed.description: After the Rustbucket breaks down, Ben, Gwen and Grandpa Max find themselves killing time at the local town library but soon scramble to out maneuver Hex as he searches for a hidden ancient artifact.

removed.title: Mud on the Run
removed.description: Ben gets a tough lesson on knowing his limits when he competes in a grueling obstacle race, made even worse by the Weatherheads!

removed.title: A Tattle Tale
removed.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP find themselves stranded on an island of tattle-tales.

removed.title: A Dame-gerous Game
removed.description: After Leshawna, Bridgette, Owen and Cody win a Hide & Seek competition, they're trapped on a private island by a jealous former champion and forced to play for their freedom.

removed.title: Beth and the Beanstalk
removed.description: After having a chocolate bar confiscated by Chef, Beth finds herself in a parallel giant world and aims to get back her now giant chocolate bar.

removed.title: Pinata Regatta
removed.description: Izzy can't bring herself to smash a Pinata during the class' Cinco De Mayo celebrations. But when that unsmashed Pinata comes to life and spawns an evil Pinata Army, it's batter up.

removed.title: Total Eclipse of the Fart
removed.description: After accidentally swallowing her first loose tooth and fearing that means no cash under the pillow, Leshawna tries to capture the tooth fairy. Instead, she accidentally captures the fart fairy. This comes with great consequence.

removed.title: Royal Flush
removed.description: When the other kids fear Harold has accidentally flushed himself down Chef's fancy new toilet, they travel into the sewer on a rescue mission. But will they find Harold before the mythical Alligator King traps them underground forever?

removed.title: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik/First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous
removed.description: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik: It's the Haavik Show! Haavik shows up unexpectedly at the practice field and proposes he and Dan play a little game. The Awesome Brawlers have never seen this man before, but they sense something is odd about him. Regardless, when Haavik strokes Dan's ego, there's no way he's backing down from this challenge./First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous: With his back against the wall, Dan tries flipping the script on Haavik by challenging him to a game of his own - a Bakugan Brawl. If Dan wins, then Haavik will have to set him, and the other Awesome Brawler's free.

removed.title: Dangerous Dealings/The Hunter Returns
removed.description: Dangerous Dealings: The Awesome Brawler's have become aware of a growing number of adults with illegal Baku-brawling devices. But where are they all coming from? Shun decides to take things into his own hands and sets up a "sting" operation to try to draw out the person selling the devices./The Hunter Returns: Lightning has been caught and locked up by an overly aggressive dog catcher! And to make things worse, he doesn't have his collar with Baku-balls. At the compound where he's being held, he runs into an old foe.  It's up to these two enemies to team up and escape their captor.

removed.title: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers/The Return of Sophie
removed.description: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers: The Awesome brawlers go to see Benton Dusk to tell him about the Fusion Bakugan and ask him if he knows anything about this character: Haavik. However, the meeting takes an unexpected twist when Haavik decides to crash it./The Return of Sophie: A video has surfaced showing Toshi using an illegal Baku-Brawling device! Shun has his hands full when Sophie starts making trouble for Kazami Holdings, accusing them of illegally exploiting Bakugan.

removed.title: Wynton's Reality Show/Bakugan Soccer
removed.description: Wynton's Reality Show: Lia has had it with Wynton's pranking, but little does she know Wynton is in for a taste of his own medicine. A prank goes too far, and Wynton finds himself in a real-life nightmare with a rampaging Bakugan!/Bakugan Soccer: The Awesome Brawlers and their Bakugan decide to have a game of Bakugan Soccer! The intensity ramps up when Pepe, his teammates and a mysterious coach show up for a little fun. It will take major teamwork for the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan to defeat this rowdy bunch.

removed.title: Farewell, Phantom Thief
removed.description: After being exposed as a phantom thief in the Bakugan battle league, the Awesome Brawlers are concerned about Ajit, but have no idea of his whereabouts. Dan is particularly affected by Ajit's disappearance and sets out to find him to get some answers./Ajit is out to set right all the wrong doings of his phantom thief past. When he attempts to break into a museum to return artifacts, his mentor Storm is waiting for him. A Bakugan brawl breaks out between two when Storm rolls out his new Bakugan: Cimoga.

removed.title: Ninjago Confidential
removed.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

removed.title: The Prodigal Father
removed.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

removed.title: The Temple of Madness
removed.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

removed.title: Game Over
removed.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

removed.title: Shintaro
removed.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

removed.title: Teddi Bear
removed.description: In an endless junkyard the Bears meet Teddi, a sentient teddy bear.

removed.title: High Baby Fashion
removed.description: The Bears enter Panda into a fashion contest, but he's got some fierce competition when Madam Malin and Madeline show up!

removed.title: A Real Crayon
removed.description: The Bears find a mysterious crayon that has the power to make anything they draw become REAL.

removed.title: Witches
removed.description: The Bears accidentally summon three mysterious witches and have to figure out how to get them back home.

removed.title: A Gross Worm
removed.description: The Bears help Unica return an endangered alien worm to its home.
